summary: There are Villains we just love, because of their attitude or their characteristics in general. But what catches us the most is...
body:
Villains who deserved better

There are Villains we just love, because of their attitude or their characteristics in general. But what catches us the most is the sad background story on how they became what they are now. Here is a list of my most favorite villains in movie, show and even books.

1. Lucifer (Supernatural)

2. Crowley (Supernatural)

3.Draco Malfoy (Harry Potter)

4. Loki (Marvel)

5. Bill Cypher (Gravity Falls)

6. Captain Hook (Book: Lost Boy by Christina Henry)

7. Kylo Ren/ Ben Solo (Star Wars)

8. Negan (The Walking Dead)


(Might add more over the time)

What are your favorite Villains?

(Btw, Viva La Vida by Coldplay is an awesome song for Villains. Just saying for those who love video editing)

title: December 24th, 1914
body:
read it on the AO3 at http://bit.ly/2YTyib1

by soft_october

“I knew I’d find you here,“ the angel’s voice is choked, desperate, “This is one of yours, it has to be one of yours-” and for once Crowley wants to lie to him as much as Aziraphale wants it to be true.
 

Hiding out from a battlefield in 1914 in uniforms of opposing sides, an angel and a demon witness both the destructive power of humanity and it’s endless capacity for love.

answer:
Yes.

Crowley used to spread bad conspiracy theories on the internet, but he ended up feeling very distressed when he realized that the theories humans came up with were far crazier than anything that could occur to him. He decided that he would instead post Tumblr gradients and caption them with something intriguing. Oh, he invented Tumblr too, though the result was worse than he anticipated.
